polations in both value and key positions, but that might just duplicate the value/key. However, there isn't an existing solution for that yet. Also, I might consider how `Json.arr` handles order preservation in arrays and the existing check for indices in those arrays.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Circe's JSON Object**\\n\\nI'm exploring whether Circe's JSON object preserves insertion order and if the public API supports this. It seems like a feature that could allow testing field order with literal and interpolated keys and values. I should check if JsonObject handles duplicate keys and top-level null fields differently, as there might be functionality around existing nested values and how top-level JSON primitives are treated without needing an enclosing array or object. This all feels quite technical!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining JSON top-level primitives**\\n\\nI’m looking into existing behaviors where top-level strings and JSON are interpolated rather than treated as literal top-level primitives. I could add tests for different primitive types like `null`, `false`, and numbers, which should help cover parsing in a `singleContext` for literal primitives. There’s a need for a distinct public feature for top-level literals, and I should ensure that all relevant classes are public. I also need to add style type annotations in functions, which feels like a lot to manage!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DWrmxVww5LG7S9IakUnjgA7K|fc_0f488e3eaffc447e016a3f998e90c8819786b6ef722aa2c885", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.circe/circe-literal_3/0.14.15/src/test/scala/io_circe/circe_literal_3/Circe_literal_3Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "    assert(stringValue(values(2)) == topLevelText)\n    assert(values(3) == Json.True)\n\n  private final case class Details(id: Int, label: String, active: Boolean)\n", "newText": "    assert(stringValue(values(2)) == topLevelText)\n    assert(values(3) == Json.True)\n\n  @Test\n  def jsonInterpolatorBuildsTopLevelPrimitiveLiterals(): Unit =\n    val topLevelNull: Json = json\"\"\"null\"\"\"\n    val topLevelBoolean: Json = json\"\"\"false\"\"\"\n    val topLevelString: Json = json\"\"\"\"literal text with π\"\"\"\"\"\"\n    val topLevelNumber: Json = json\"\"\"-9876543210.125e2\"\"\"\n\n    assert(topLevelNull == Json.Null)\n    assert(topLevelBoolean == Json.False)\n    assert(stringValue(topLevelString) == \"literal text with π\")\n    assert(decoded[BigDecimal](topLevelNumber) == BigDecimal(\"-9876543210.125e2\"))\n\n  private final case class Details(id: Int, label: String, active: Boolean)\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3451, "output": 1312, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44187, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782552954111, "responseId": "resp_0f488e3eaffc447e016a3f997a99808197a3057e017e81bcea"}}
